# Code Pattern Reviewer

Review code for design pattern usage, anti-patterns, and structural improvements.

## Anti-Pattern Detection Checklist

Scan code for these signals before giving recommendations:

| Signal | What to Look For | Anti-Pattern |
|--------|-----------------|--------------|
| File >200 lines | Line count | God Object |
| Class with 15+ methods | Method count | God Object → Facade + decompose |
| Repeated `switch`/`if` on type | `switch.*type`, `if.*instanceof` | Missing Factory/Strategy |
| `new ClassName()` in business logic | Direct instantiation | Missing Factory/DI |
| Nesting >4 levels deep | Indentation depth | Spaghetti → Chain of Responsibility |
| Same pattern used for every problem | Singleton/Observer everywhere | Golden Hammer |
| Circular imports between modules | Import graph | Missing Mediator/layered arch |
| No error boundaries | Scattered try/catch | Missing Chain of Responsibility |
| Services calling each other directly | Cross-service tight coupling | Missing Facade/Anti-Corruption Layer |

## Findings Table Format

Always output a findings table:

```
| # | Severity | Anti-Pattern / Issue | Location | Pattern Suggestion |
|---|----------|---------------------|----------|--------------------|
| 1 | Critical  | God Object (450 lines) | `UserService.ts:1` | Facade + split services |
| 2 | High      | Type switch repeated  | `factory.ts:34` | Factory Method |
| 3 | Medium    | Direct `new` in handler | `order.ts:12` | Dependency Injection |
| 4 | Low       | No retry on external call | `api.ts:88` | Retry + Circuit Breaker |
```

Severity: **Critical** (breaks scalability) → **High** (significant debt) → **Medium** (smell) → **Low** (style)

## Pattern Improvement Map

When an anti-pattern is found, suggest the corrective pattern:

| Anti-Pattern | Corrective Pattern |
|-------------|-------------------|
| God Object | Facade + single-responsibility services |
| Missing abstraction over creation | Factory Method / Abstract Factory |
| Scattered algorithm variants | Strategy |
| Tight event coupling | Observer / Event Bus |
| Cross-service coupling | Facade / Anti-Corruption Layer |
| No failure isolation | Circuit Breaker / Bulkhead |
| Mixed read/write in one model | CQRS |
| Lost audit trail | Event Sourcing |

